{"markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"","pagetitle":"Software — Lucia S. Layritz"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n  <p class=\"category\">Software</p>\n  <h1>Software</h1>\n  <p style=\"max-width:600px; color:#444; margin-top:0.8rem;\">\n    Open-source code accompanying research papers, side projects, and tools. \n    Most work is in R and Python; some JavaScript.\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"project-grid\">\n\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/lucialayr/disturbanceBorealLPJ\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"border-bottom:none;\">\n    <div class=\"project-card\">\n      <p class=\"lang\">R</p>\n      <h3>disturbanceBorealLPJ</h3>\n      <p>Reproduction code for the boreal forest disturbance and climate change paper (Biogeosciences, 2025).</p>\n    </div>\n  </a>\n\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/lucialayr/stableEWS_paper\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"border-bottom:none;\">\n    <div class=\"project-card\">\n      <p class=\"lang\">R</p>\n      <h3>stableEWS_paper</h3>\n      <p>Reproduction of the early warning signs paper — tipping points with non-Gaussian-stable noise (Scientific Reports, 2025).</p>\n    </div>\n  </a>\n\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/lucialayr/alphastableTransient\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"border-bottom:none;\">\n    <div class=\"project-card\">\n      <p class=\"lang\">Jupyter / Python</p>\n      <h3>alphastableTransient</h3>\n      <p>Code for \"Disturbances and long transients create illusion of stable states\".</p>\n    </div>\n  </a>\n\n\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/lucialayr/borealRecovery\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"border-bottom:none;\">\n    <div class=\"project-card\">\n      <p class=\"lang\">R</p>\n      <h3>borealRecovery</h3>\n      <p>Analysis code for post-disturbance boreal forest recovery modelling.</p>\n    </div>\n  </a>\n\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/lucialayr/backgammon\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"border-bottom:none;\">\n    <div class=\"project-card\">\n      <p class=\"lang\">JavaS